[Given that this dengue 2 virus epidemic has been occurring since at least
May and likely before that, the use of single serum IgM or IgG assays for
diagnosis will provide inaccurate diagnoses. Basing such diagnoses on such
tests in an area in which other, clinically undifferentiated, illnesses are
also occurring, these numbers cannot be considered definitive. Tony has
used the term "probable", which is correct, but more definitive testing is
required. If eight specimens were confirmed by EIA (whatever that means)
or PCR, it would be useful to know how many were tested, i.e., 8/8 or 8/?.
